They‚Äôre not super common, though‚ÄîSingapore‚Äôs urban environment limits their presence, and there are likely only a small number around, possibly stragglers from larger populations in nearby Malaysia or Indonesia. Encounters are infrequent enough to grab headlines when they happen. So, while they‚Äôre definitely there, you‚Äôre not likely to see one unless you‚Äôre in the right wild or semi-wild areas at the right time!

